sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MutWH as odh-notebook-controller<br/>Mutating Webhook<br/>8443/TCP TLS
    participant KFCtrl as kf-notebook-controller<br/>Reconciler
    participant ODHCtrl as odh-notebook-controller<br/>Reconciler
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Sidecar 8443/TCP TLS
    participant Jupyter as Notebook Container<br/>Jupyter 8888/TCP
    participant CullingCtrl as Culling Controller

    Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: Notebook Creation and Ingress Setup

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Bearer Token (user)
    K8sAPI->>MutWH: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>mTLS (API server cert)
    Note right of MutWH: Injects: kube-rbac-proxy sidecar,<br/>CA cert bundles,<br/>Elyra pipeline config,<br/>MLflow env vars,<br/>ImageStream resolution,<br/>proxy env vars,<br/>reconciliation lock
    MutWH-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook CR
    K8sAPI-->>User: Notebook created

    KFCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet (1 replica)<br/>ServiceAccount token
    KFCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterIP Service<br/>(80/TCP → 8888)

    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute<br/>(controller namespace)<br/>ServiceAccount token
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ReferenceGrant<br/>(cross-namespace)
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create kube-rbac-proxy Service<br/>(8443/TCP, TLS)
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterRoleBinding<br/>(auth-delegator)

    Note over User,Jupyter: External Access Path

    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}/<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>RBACProxy: Forward request<br/>HTTPS TLS (service-ca)
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(get notebooks in namespace)
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: Allowed
    RBACProxy->>Jupyter: Forward to 8888/TCP<br/>HTTP (localhost, pre-authenticated)
    Jupyter-->>RBACProxy: Response
    RBACProxy-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Response

    Note over CullingCtrl,Jupyter: Flow 2: Idle Notebook Culling

    loop Every IDLENESS_CHECK_PERIOD minutes
        CullingCtrl->>Jupyter: GET /api/kernels<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP (in-cluster)
        Jupyter-->>CullingCtrl: Kernel activity data
        CullingCtrl->>Jupyter: GET /api/terminals<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP
        Jupyter-->>CullingCtrl: Terminal activity data
    end

    Note right of CullingCtrl: If idle > CULL_IDLE_TIME
    CullingCtrl->>K8sAPI: Update Notebook annotation<br/>(kubeflow-resource-stopped)
    KFCtrl->>K8sAPI: Scale StatefulSet replicas=0<br/>ServiceAccount token
